column5: Hey guys im back from guiding... I don't have much to say about the place so here are some pics  Geting there        41"  38"  43"  Some walleye  381/2"  Same one 381/2"  40"  Same 40" And man he is FAT (sorry for the bad pic)  Snow in June lol  A friend that likes the camp  The end of the day  Going out guiding  Just a nice pic  I don't have to tell you guys what this is    There are some pics for you guys thanks for looking
Back already??? That wasn't worth the 100LL to get you there!  Nice fishy pics though!!
Yeah I'm back already that's y I say I don't have much to say about the place lol  Thanks yeah we got some good fish!
Nice mess of Walleye and some beauty pike! Looks like you had a blast
At least the fishing and scenery was good....
The wilderness makes it all worthwhile! Awesome pictures.
Thanks guys ya it was I good trip all in all
Sounds like you quit working at a fishing lodge recently as well...welcome to the club  Was it the crap pay, the long hours or the terrible living conditions?

This was lodge # 2 for me the 1st one was good I was the #1 guide there and still could have been the now one was a Joke the boss was an ass and the terrible living conditions but the $ was good... I just told myself I'll come home and do tournaments and have a fun summer  What lodge did you work at?
